    "image_with_text_RyBnnm": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_KcGpTB": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Wild Gardens to Rewilding"
          }
        },
        "text_r4bhaE": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>That philosophy has continued to evolve into something even more radical. At <a href=\"https://knepp.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://knepp.co.uk/\">Knepp Estate</a>, former farmland has been transformed into a thriving, self-willed ecosystem. Here, nature is largely left to its own devices, creating rich biodiversity and a powerful sense of ecological renewal.</p><p>It feels like the natural extension of <a href=\"https://www.gravetyemanor.co.uk/the-manor-gardens/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.gravetyemanor.co.uk/the-manor-gardens/\">William Robinson’s</a> thinking - trusting nature not just in planting, but at scale, animals and all.</p><p>This sense of balance between human life and the natural world runs deeply through British landscape culture, and is something that also resonates in the world of Molly Mahon, whose home near <a href=\"https://ashdownforestfdn.org/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://ashdownforestfdn.org/\">Ashdown Forest</a> reflects a daily closeness to shifting seasons, wildlife and the rhythms of the land.</p>",
            "code": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_KcGpTB",
        "text_r4bhaE"
      ],
